Shredder woke up a while ago, Quickstrike. He isn't knocked out anymore.

::Prowl/Zardus/Zenyak/Shredder::

Prowl catches his breath as Iron Raptor brushes against his shoulder, his 
witty responce dying on his lips.

He shakes his head to clear it of the feeling that he was falling. What was 
going on? He was in a dangerous situation and yet he couldn't concentrate! He 
clenches his teeth.

Prowl keeps moving stealthily through the forest, trying to figure out what 
was wrong with him.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Zardus walks into the bridge of the alliance base, fully healead and 
functional. He looks at the scanners, noticing the new maximal ship, and also 
the newly arrived maximal and predacon signatures (The dinobots at the 
gestalt group).

His eyes narrow as he looks at the scanners again. He raises his comm-link to 
his mouth. "Nemesis, as soon as you are repaired, please join me at the 
bridge."
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Zenyak opens his eyes. He was laying on his stomach in a pile of seaweed. He 
gets up, rubbing his head.

"Computer, how long was I out?"

After several seconds of computation, his internal computer reports that an 
estimate was not possible. He growls and looks down at his wounds. Striker 
had busted him up pretty good, he had to admit that.

"Slagging maximal," He grumbles to himself as he walks off through the forest.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Shredder looks at the predacon base. He chuckles. If he could get in, he 
could do quite alot of damage. And the computer wouldn't recognize him as an 
enemy, thanks to Quickstrike. Due to a malfunction in his comm-link, he 
didn't hear Quickstrike's last message, not knowing that the autoguns indeed 
had different orders.

He walks on, confident, when an autogun swirls around, aiming at his chest. 
Shredder's eyes widen.

In several seconds, he is laying on the wreck of a tree that he was blow into 
by the autogun.

He gets up, a severe pain present in his chest. He looks at the predacon base 
and puts his comm-link to his mouth.

"Quickstrike, disable the autoguns, I need to get in!"
